article.headline: Rhode Island 92, Northeastern 72
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. (AP) -- Parfait Bitee and Jimmy Baron scored 17 points each to help the University of Rhode Island defeat Northeastern University 92-72 on Wednesday night. Joe Mbang scored 16 points and Keith Cothran had 15 as Rhode Island's head coach Jim Baron notched his 300th career win. The Huskies were led by Matt Janning, who scored 34 points. Manny Adako added 12 points and eight rebounds, while Nkem Ojougboh pulled down 10 rebounds. Northeastern (2-3) led early and the teams played tight until Rhode Island (7-1) outscored the Huskies 10-6 to take a 45-36 lead at the half. With the game tied at 59 with 11:57 to play, Rhode Island went on a 21-5 run over a 7:34 span, turning the close game into a rout.
